ce:section.ce:para:
With the growing application of fluorescence anti-counterfeiting technology, the CDs have been a promising candidate for anti-counterfeiting marking [48]. The applicability of F-NCDs as fluorescent anti-counterfeiting film and ink was investigated (Fig. 8
                        ). Fig. 8a showed the high transparent and bright fluorescent performance of the F-NCDs-PVA film under day light (ii) and UV (365 nm) light (iii), respectively, and the blue emission color of the film was similar with F-NCDs solution. The SEM image and element fraction of the F-NCDs-PVA film was shown in Fig. S9, the 2.13 wt% of N from F-NCDs indicated that F-NCDs was greatly dispersed and enabled solid-state fluorescence (UV to blue) light conversion in PVA media. The invisible F-NCDs-PVA ink was used to print different shapes (art pictures, Chinese words and English characters) on three substrates, including polypropylene board, pulp board and calcium silicate board (Fig. 8b-d). The F-NCDs-PVA ink exhibited bright blue fluorescence under UV (365 nm) light. In order to confirm the resistance of the films and printed characters, which were exposed to different temperature (−40 °C ~ 80 °C) for 12 h and UV light (365 nm) for different times (2–8 h) (Fig. 9
                        ). There was no visible attenuation of fluorescence in the optical images of films and printable characters at different temperatures and aging times. The PL intensity of fluorescent films were also recorded and stabilized around 54,000 cps at different temperature and aging times (Fig. S10). These indicated that the great photostability of our anti-counterfeiting materials. Therefore, the obtained fluorescent films and invisible ink from F-NCDs can be used for anti-counterfeiting applications.
